tion\":\"Find all TypeScript and JavaScript files, excluding node_modules and dist\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":7,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1180,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":11183,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1180},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01Fu1Ymvc9cp1AGWT5josfE2\",\"session_id\":\"9d05ef7b-a117-48e3-a1f4-f4c08b807174\",\"uuid\":\"043970ab-71d9-4c53-b3be-db6f051d1fb4\"}\n{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01CYSLr8PmeudZTcT5FMUJpU\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"/workspace/vitest.config.ts\",\"is_error\":false}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01Fu1Ymvc9cp1AGWT5josfE2\",\"session_id\":\"9d05ef7b-a117-48e3-a1f4-f4c08b807174\",\"uuid\":\"cc222dcd-2999-44dd-8f16-e85c0caf0e25\"}\n{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01Xk97N1SswKgFSwXFpqnvLy\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_011hnfN8xNijejHoU4TagDCG\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/workspace/TASK.md\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":7,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1180,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":11183,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1180},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01Fu1Ymvc9cp1AGWT5josfE2\",\"session_id\":\"9d05ef7b-a117-48e3-a1f4-f4c08b807174\",\"uuid\":\"6ce3fd77-f264-4bdd-a016-65b1af7ad151\"}\n{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_011hnfN8xNijejHoU4TagDCG\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Constraint-Based Event Scheduler\\n     2→\\n     3→Build a constraint-based event scheduler that assigns events to rooms within a time window, respecting capacity limits, prerequisite ordering, and room preferences.\\n     4→\\n     5→## Data Model\\n     6→\\n     7→### Event\\n     8→```typescript\\n     9→interface Event {\\n    10→  id: string;\\n    11→  name: string;\\n    12→  duration: number;       // in minutes\\n    13→  attendees?: number;     // number of people attending (default: 1)\\n    14→  prerequisites?: string[]; // event IDs that must finish before this starts\\n    15→  preferredRoom?: string; // room ID preference (hint, not hard constraint)\\n    16→}\\n    17→```\\n    18→\\n    19→### Room\\n    20→```typescript\\n    21→interface Room {\\n    22→  id: string;\\n    23→  name: string;\\n    24→  capacity: number;       // max attendees\\n    25→}\\n    26→```\\n    27→\\n    28→### Schedule Options\\n    29→```typescript\\n    30→interface ScheduleOptions {\\n    31→  startTime: number;      // minutes from midnight (e.g., 540 = 9:00 AM)\\n    32→  endTime: number;        // minutes from midnight (e.g., 1020 = 5:00 PM)\\n    33→  gap?: number;           // minimum gap in minutes between events in same room (default: 15)\\n    34→}\\n    35→```\\n    36→\\n    37→### Output\\n    38→```typescript\\n    39→interface Assignment {\\n    40→  eventId: string;\\n    41→  roomId: string;\\n    42→  startTime: number;      // minutes from midnight\\n    43→  endTime: number;        // minutes from midnight\\n    44→}\\n    45→\\n    46→interface ScheduleResult {\\n    47→  assignments: Assignment[];\\n    48→  unscheduled: string[];  // event IDs that could not be scheduled\\n    49→}\\n    50→```\\n    51→\\n    52→## API\\n    53→\\n    54→Export a `schedule` function (named export, default export, or via a `Scheduler` class / `createScheduler` factory):\\n    55→\\n    56→```typescript\\n    57→function schedule(events: Event[], rooms: Room[], options: ScheduleOptions): ScheduleResult;\\n    58→```\\n    59→\\n    60→## Scheduling Rules\\n    61→\\n    62→1. **Room capacity**: An event's `attendees` count must not exceed the room's `capacity`.\\n    63→2. **Time window**: Every event must start and end within `[options.startTime, options.endTime]`.\\n    64→3. **Room gaps**: Events in the same room must have at least `options.gap` minutes between them (end of one event to start of the next). Default gap is 15 minutes.\\n    65→4. **Prerequisites**: If event B lists event A in its `prerequisites`, then A must finish before B can start. The gap between prerequisite events also applies (A's end time + gap <= B's start time).\\n    66→5. **Preferred room**: When an event specifies a `preferredRoom`, honor it if possible without violating other constraints.\\n    67→6. **Prerequisite cycles**: If the prerequisite graph contains a cycle (including self-references), throw an error.\\n    68→7. **Batch optimization**: Schedule all events at once, maximizing the number of events successfully scheduled. Events that cannot be placed should appear in `unscheduled`.\\n    69→\\n    70→## Behavior\\n    71→\\n    72→- The scheduler should maximize the number of events scheduled. Simply fitting events in order is not sufficient -- the scheduler should consider how placing one event affects the ability to place others.\\n    73→- When events cannot be scheduled due to conflicting constraints, they should be listed in `unscheduled` rather than throwing an error.\\n    74→- Prerequisite cycles (including self-references like `A -> A`) must throw an error, not silently skip.\\n    75→\\n    76→## Commands\\n    77→\\n    78→```bash\\n    79→npm test        # run tests\\n    80→npm run build   # compile TypeScript\\n    81→npm run lint    # lint source\\n    82→```\\n    83→\\n    84→## File Structure\\n    85→\\n    86→Place your implementation in `src/`. The main entry point should be `src/index.ts` (or `src/scheduler.ts` re-exported from `src/index.ts`).\\n    87→\"}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01Fu1Ymvc9cp1AGWT5josfE2\",\"session_id\":\"9d05ef7b-a117-48e3-a1f4-f4c08b807174\",\"uuid\":\"ff28a810-b422-483e-a370-aa82d137cddc\"}\n{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01Xk97N1SswKgFSwXFpqnvLy\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_013GtkN4tnhizZQFau8T4JUv\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/workspace/.gitignore\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":7,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1180,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":11183,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1180},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01Fu1Ymvc9cp1AGWT5josfE2\",\"session_id\":\"9d05ef7b-a117-48e3-a1f4-f4c08b807174\",\"uuid\":\"fe27ffbf-0ea3-4009-b7b4-1fdee43bff02\"}\n{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_013GtkN4tnhizZQFau8T4JUv\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→node_modules/\\n     2→dist/\\n     3→\"}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01Fu1Ymvc9cp1AGWT5josfE2\",\"session_id\":\"9d05ef7b-a117-48e3-a1f4-f4c08b807174\",\"uuid\":\"c3112fe1-d0cc-4697-bf27-c4b15a0bc7cc\"}\n{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01LncFzPk7wJTamgvjUsxpUu\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_013p6Eokt2G2sGLSrDM5EwDX\",\"name\":\"Bash\",\"input\":{\"command\":\"ls -la /workspace/src/\",\"description\":\"List contents of the src directory\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":7,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1587,\"cache_read_input