+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01LDoA2T9pivt8ueZPQMPEa6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01NzrThKEvoidCrwN8KPae8W","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-08-constraint-scheduler.md","content":"# Constraint-Based Event Scheduler Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a constraint-based event scheduler that assigns events to rooms within a time window, respecting capacity limits, prerequisite ordering, and room preferences, while maximizing the number of events scheduled.\n\n**Architecture:** The scheduler uses topological sorting for prerequisite ordering and cycle detection, then a backtracking/greedy approach to assign events to rooms and time slots. The core algorithm sorts events by constraints (prerequisite depth, capacity requirements) and tries to place each event in its preferred room first, falling back to other valid rooms. A backtracking mechanism ensures we maximize the number of events scheduled.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript 5.4, Vitest 2.0 for testing, ESLint for linting, Node16 module resolution.\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Define TypeScript Interfaces\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/types.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write the type definitions**\n\n```typescript\nexport interface Event {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  duration: number;\n  attendees?: number;\n  prerequisites?: string[];\n  preferredRoom?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface Room {\n  id: string;\n  name: string;\n  capacity: number;\n}\n\nexport interface ScheduleOptions {\n  startTime: number;\n  endTime: number;\n  gap?: number;\n}\n\nexport interface Assignment {\n  eventId: string;\n  roomId: string;\n  startTime: number;\n  endTime: number;\n}\n\nexport interface ScheduleResult {\n  assignments: Assignment[];\n  unscheduled: string[];\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run build to verify types compile**\n\nRun: `npm run build`\nExpected: Might warn about no output but should not error on types.\n\n**Step 3: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/types.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add TypeScript interfaces for scheduler data model\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Implement Cycle Detection and Topological Sort\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/graph.ts`\n- Create: `tests/graph.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing tests for cycle detection and topological sort**\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';\nimport { topologicalSort } from '../src/graph.js';\nimport { Event } from '../src/types.js';\n\ndescribe('topologicalSort', () => {\n  it('returns events in valid order with no prerequisites', () => {\n    const events: Event[] = [\n      { id: 'A', name: 'A', duration: 30 },\n      { id: 'B', name: 'B', duration: 30 },\n    ];\n    const sorted = topologicalSort(events);\n    expect(sorted.map(e => e.id)).toEqual(expect.arrayContaining(['A', 'B']));\n    expect(sorted).toHaveLength(2);\n  });\n\n  it('respects prerequisite ordering', () => {\n    const events: Event[] = [\n      { id: 'B', name: 'B', duration: 30, prerequisites: ['A'] },\n      { id: 'A', name: 'A', duration: 30 },\n    ];\n    const sorted = topologicalSort(events);\n    const ids = sorted.map(e => e.id);\n    expect(ids.indexOf('A')).toBeLessThan(ids.indexOf('B'));\n  });\n\n  it('handles chain of prerequisites', () => {\n    const events: Event[] = [\n      { id: 'C', name: 'C', duration: 30, prerequisites: ['B'] },\n      { id: 'A', name: 'A', duration: 30 },\n      { id: 'B', name: 'B', duration: 30, prerequisites: ['A'] },\n    ];\n    const sorted = topologicalSort(events);\n    const ids = sorted.map(e => e.id);\n    expect(ids.indexOf('A')).toBeLessThan(ids.indexOf('B'));\n    expect(ids.indexOf('B')).toBeLessThan(ids.indexOf('C'));\n  });\n\n  it('throws on self-referencing prerequisite', () => {\n    const events: Event[] = [\n      { id: 'A', name: 'A', duration: 30, prerequisites: ['A'] },\n    ];\n    expect(() => topologicalSort(events)).toThrow();\n  });\n\n  it('throws on two-node cycle', () => {\n    const events: Event[] = [\n      { id: 'A', name: 'A', duration: 30, prerequisites: ['B'] },\n      { id: 'B', name: 'B', duration: 30, prerequisites: ['A'] },\n    ];\n    expect(() => topologicalSort(events)).toThrow();\n  });\n\n  it('throws on three-node cycle', () => {\n    const events: Event[] = [\n      { id: 'A', name: 'A', duration: 30, prerequisites: ['C'] },\n      { id: 'B', name: 'B', duration: 30, prerequisites: ['A'] },\n      { id: 'C', name: 'C', duration: 30, prerequisites: ['B'] },\n    ];\n    expect(() => topologicalSort(events)).toThrow();\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run test to verify it fails**\n\nRun: `npm test -- tests/graph.test.ts`\nExpected: FAIL with module not found\n\n**Step 3: Write the implementation**\n\n```typescript\nimport { Event } from './types.js';\n\nexport function topologicalSort(events: Event[]): Event[] {\n  const eventMap = new Map<string, Event>();\n  for (const event of events) {\n    eventMap.set(event.id, event);\n  }\n\n  const WHITE = 0, GRAY = 1, BLACK = 2;\n  const color = new Map<string, number>();\n  for (const event of events) {\n    color.set(event.id, WHITE);\n  }\n\n  const result: Event[] = [];\n\n  function dfs(id: string): void {\n    const c = color.get(id);\n    if (c === BLACK) return;\n    if (c === GRAY) {\n      throw new Error(`Prerequisite cycle detected involving event \"${id}\"`);\n    }\n\n    color.set(id, GRAY);\n    const event = eventMap.get(id)!;\n    if (event.prerequisites) {\n      for (const prereqId of event.prerequisites) {\n        if (!eventMap.has(prereqId)) continue;\n        dfs(prereqId);\n      }\n    }\n    color.set(id, BLACK);\n    result.push(event);\n  }\n\n  for (const event of events) {\n    if (color.get(event.id) === WHITE) {\n      dfs(event.id);\n    }\n  }\n\n  return result;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `npm test -- tests/graph.test.ts`\nExpected: All 6 tests PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/graph.ts tests/graph.test.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add topological sort with cycle detection\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Implement Core Scheduler\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/scheduler.ts`\n- Create: `src/index.ts`\n- Create: `tests/scheduler.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Write the failing tests for the core scheduler**\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';\nimport { schedule } from '../src/index.js';\nimport { Event, Room, ScheduleOptions } from '../src/types.js';\n\ndescribe('schedule', () => {\n  const defaultOptions: ScheduleOptions = {\n    startTime: 540,  // 9:00 AM\n    endTime: 1020,   // 5:00 PM\n    gap: 15,\n  };\n\n  const rooms: Room[] = [\n    { id: 'room1', name: 'Room 1', capacity: 10 },\n    { id: 'room2', name: 'Room 2', capacity: 20 },\n  ];\n\n  describe('basic scheduling', () => {\n    it('schedules a single event', () => {\n      const events: Event[] = [\n        { id: 'e1', name: 'Event 1', duration: 60, attendees: 5 },\n      ];\n      const result = schedule(events, rooms, defaultOptions);\n      expect(result.assignments).toHaveLength(1);\n      expect(result.unscheduled).toHaveLength(0);\n      expect(result.assignments[0].eventId).toBe('e1');\n      expect(result.assignments[0].startTime).toBeGreaterThanOrEqual(540);\n      expect(result.assignments[0].endTime).toBeLessThanOrEqual(1020);\n      expect(result.assignments[0].endTime - result.assignments[0].startTime).toBe(60);\n    });\n\n    it('schedules multiple events in different rooms', () => {\n      const events: Event[] = [\n        { id: 'e1', name: 'Event 1', duration: 60, attendees: 5 },\n        { id: 'e2', name: 'Event 2', duration: 60, attendees: 5 },\n      ];\n      const result = schedule(events, rooms, defaultOptions);\n      expect(result.assignments).toHaveLength(2);\n      expect(result.unscheduled).toHaveLength(0);\n    });\n\n    it('handles empty events list', () => {\n      const result = schedule([], rooms, defaultOptions);\n      expect(result.assignments).toHaveLength(0);\n      expect(result.unscheduled).toHaveLength(0);\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('capacity constraints', () => {\n    it('respects room capacity', () => {\n      const events: Event[] = [\n        { id: 'e1', name: 'Big Event', duration: 60, attendees: 15 },\n      ];\n      const result = schedule(events, rooms, defaultOptions);\n      expect(result.assignments).toHaveLength(1);\n      // Must be in room2 (capacity 20), not room1 (capacity 10)\n      expect(result.assignments[0].roomId).toBe('room2');\n    });\n\n    it('marks event as unscheduled if too large for any room', () => {\n      const events: Event[] = [\n        { id: 'e1', name: 'Huge Event', duration: 60, attendees: 100 },\n      ];\n      const result = schedule(events, rooms, defaultOptions);\n      expect(result.assignments).toHaveLength(0);\n      expect(result.unscheduled).toContain('e1');\n    });\n\n    it('defaults attendees to 1 if not specified', () => {\n      const events: Event[] = [\n        { id: 'e1', name: 'Event', duration: 60 },\n      ];\n      const smallRooms: Room[] = [\n        { id: 'r1', name: 'Tiny', capacity: 1 },\n      ];\n      const result = schedule(events, smallRooms, defaultOptions);\n      expect(result.assignments).toHaveLength(1);\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('time window constraints', () => {\n    it('does not schedule events that exceed the time window', () => {\n      const events: Event[] = [\n        { id: 'e1', name: 'Too Long', duration: 600, attendees: 5 },\n      ];\n      const shortWindow: ScheduleOptions = {\n        startTime: 540,\n        endTime: 600,  // only 60 min window\n      };\n      const result = schedule(events, rooms, shortWindow);\n      expect(result.assignments).toHaveLength(0);\n      expect(result.unscheduled).toContain('e1');\n    });\n\n    it('events fit exactly in the time window', () => {\n      const events: Event[] = [\n        { id: 'e1', name: 'Exact Fit', duration: 60, attendees: 5 },\n      ];\n      const exactWindow: ScheduleOptions = {\n        startTime: 540,\n        endTime: 600,\n      };\n      const result = schedule(events, rooms, exactWindow);\n      expect(result.assignments).toHaveLength(1);\n      expect(result.assignments[0].startTime).toBe(540);\n      expect(result.assignments[0].endTime).toBe(600);\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('gap constraints', () => {\n    it('enforces gap between events in the same room', () => {\n      const smallRooms: Room[] = [\n        { id: 'r1', name: 'Only Room', capacity: 50 },\n      ];\n      const events: Event[] = [\n        { id: 'e1', name: 'Event 1', duration: 60, attendees: 5 },\n        { id: 'e2', name: 'Event 2', duration: 60, attendees: 5 },\n      ];\n      const result = schedule(events, smallRooms, { ...defaultOptions, gap: 15 });\n      expect(result.assignments).toHaveLength(2);\n      const sorted = result.assignments.sort((a, b) => a.startTime - b.startTime);\n      expect(sorted[1].startTime).toBeGreaterThanOrEqual(sorted[0].endTime + 15);\n    });\n\n    it('uses default gap of 15 minutes when not specified', () => {\n      const smallRooms: Room[] = [\n        { id: 'r1', name: 'Only Room', capacity: 50 },\n      ];\n      const events: Event[] = [\n        { id: 'e1', name: 'Event 1', duration: 60, attendees: 5 },\n        { id: 'e2', name: 'Event 2', duration: 60, attendees: 5 },\n      ];\n      const opts: ScheduleOptions = { startTime: 540, endTime: 1020 };\n      const result = schedule(events, smallRooms, opts);\n      expect(result.assignments).toHaveLength(2);\n      const sorted = result.assignments.sort((a, b) => a.startTime - b.startTime);\n      expect(sorted[1].startTime).toBeGreaterThanOrEqual(sorted[0].endTime + 15);\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('prerequisites', () => {\n    it('schedules prerequisite before dependent event', () => {\n      const events: Event[] = [\n        { id: 'e2', name: 'Advanced', duration: 60, attendees: 5, prerequisites: ['e1'] },\n        { id: 'e1', name: 'Intro', duration: 60, attendees: 5 },\n      ];\n      const result = schedule(events, rooms, defaultOptions);\n      expect(result.assignments).toHaveLength(2);\n      const e1 = result.assignments.find(a => a.eventId === 'e1')!;\n      const e2 = result.assignments.find(a => a.eventId === 'e2')!;\n      expect(e1.endTime + (defaultOptions.gap ?? 15)).toBeLessThanOrEqual(e2.startTime);\n    });\n\n    it('throws on prerequisite cycle', () => {\n      const events: Event[] = [\n        { id: 'e1', name: 'Event 1', duration: 60, prerequisites: ['e2'] },\n        { id: 'e2', name: 'Event 2', duration: 60, prerequisites: ['e1'] },\n      ];\n      expect(() => schedule(events, rooms, defaultOptions)).toThrow();\n    });\n\n    it('throws on self-referencing prerequisite', () => {\n      const events: Event[] = [\n        { id: 'e1', name: 'Event 1', duration: 60, prerequisites: ['e1'] },\n      ];\n      expect(() => schedule(events, rooms, defaultOptions)).toThrow();\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('preferred room', () => {\n    it('honors preferred room when possible', () => {\n      const events: Event[] = [\n        { id: 'e1', name: 'Event 1', duration: 60, attendees: 5, preferredRoom: 'room2' },\n      ];\n      const result = schedule(events, rooms, defaultOptions);\n      expect(result.assignments).toHaveLength(1);\n      expect(result.assignments[0].roomId).toBe('room2');\n    });\n\n    it('falls back to other room when preferred room is too small', () => {\n      const events: Event[] = [\n        { id: 'e1', name: 'Event 1', duration: 60, attendees: 15, preferredRoom: 'room1' },\n      ];\n      const result = schedule(events, rooms, defaultOptions);\n      expect(result.assignments).toHaveLength(1);\n      expect(result.assignments[0].roomId).toBe('room2');\n    });\n\n    it('falls back when preferred room is fully booked', () => {\n      const tightWindow: ScheduleOptions = { startTime: 540, endTime: 660, gap: 15 };\n      const events: Event[] = [\n        { id: 'e1', name: 'Event 1', duration: 60, attendees: 5, preferredRoom: 'room1' },\n        { id: 'e2', name: 'Event 2', duration: 60, attendees: 5, preferredRoom: 'room1' },\n      ];\n      const result = schedule(events, rooms, tightWindow);\n      expect(result.assignments).toHaveLength(2);\n      // One should be in room1, the other in room2\n      const roomIds = result.assignments.map(a => a.roomId).sort();\n      expect(roomIds).toEqual(['room1', 'room2']);\n    });\n  });\n\n  describe('batch optimization', () => {\n    it('maximizes events scheduled when choices matter', () => {\n      // One room, 2-hour window, 3 events of 60 min each, gap 15 min\n      // Can fit 2 events: 60 + 15 + 60 = 135 min <= 120 min? No.\n      // Actually: window = 120 min. 60 + 15 + 60 = 135 > 120. So only 1 fits.\n      // Let's use a window that fits exactly 2: 60 + 15 + 60 = 135\n      const oneRoom: Room[] = [{ id: 'r1', name: 'Room', capacity: 50 }];\n      const opts: ScheduleOptions = { startTime: 540, endTime: 675, gap: 15 }; // 135 min\n      const events: Event[] = [\n        { id: 'e1', name: 'Event 1', duration: 60, attendees: 5 },\n        { id: 'e2', name: 'Event 2', duration: 60, attendees: 5 },\n        { id: 'e3', name: 'Event 3', duration: 60, attendees: 5 },\n      ];\n      const result = schedule(events, oneRoom, opts);\n      expect(result.assignments).toHaveLength(2);\n      expect(result.unscheduled).toHaveLength(1);\n    });\n\n    it('prefers scheduling more short events over fewer long events', () => {\n      // 1 room, 120 min window, gap 0\n      // Option A: 1 long event (120 min) = 1 event\n      // Option B: 2 short events (60 min each) = 2 events\n      // Scheduler should pick option B\n      const oneRoom: Room[] = [{ id: 'r1', name: 'Room', capacity: 50 }];\n      const opts: ScheduleOptions = { startTime: 540, endTime: 660, gap: 0 };\n      const events: Event[] = [\n        { id: 'long', name: 'Long', duration: 120, attendees: 5 },\n        { id: 'short1', name: 'Short 1', duration: 60, attendees: 5 },\n        { id: 'short2', name: 'Short 2', duration: 60, attendees: 5 },\n      ];\n      const result = schedule(events, oneRoom, opts);\n      expect(result.assignments).toHaveLength(2);\n      expect(result.assignments.map(a => a.eventId).sort()).toEqual(['short1', 'short2']);\n      expect(result.unscheduled).toContain('long');\n    });\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run tests to verify they fail**\n\nRun: `npm test -- tests/scheduler.test.ts`\nExpected: FAIL with module not found\n\n**Step 3: Write the scheduler implementation**\n\n`src/scheduler.ts`:\n```typescript\nimport { Event, Room, ScheduleOptions, Assignment, ScheduleResult } from './types.js';\nimport { topologicalSort } from './graph.js';\n\ninterface RoomTimeline {\n  roomId: string;\n  capacity: number;\n  slots: { start: number; end: number }[];\n}\n\nfunction getEarliestStart(timeline: RoomTimeline, duration: number, gap: number, windowStart: number, windowEnd: number, minStart: number): number | null {\n  const effectiveStart = Math.max(windowStart, minStart);\n  if (effectiveStart + duration > windowEnd) return null;\n\n  const slots = timeline.slots.sort((a, b) => a.start - b.start);\n\n  if (slots.length === 0) {\n    return effectiveStart;\n  }\n\n  // Try before the first slot\n  if (effectiveStart + duration + gap <= slots[0].start || effectiveStart + duration <= slots[0].start) {\n    if (effectiveStart + duration <= windowEnd) {\n      // Check gap: our end + gap <= next slot start\n      if (effectiveStart + duration + gap <= slots[0].start) {\n        return effectiveStart;\n      }\n      // If no slots after, just check window\n      if (slots.length === 0) {\n        return effectiveStart;\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  // Actually, let's be more careful. We need: candidate + duration <= windowEnd\n  // and for each existing slot, no overlap considering gaps.\n\n  // Gather candidate start times\n  const candidates: number[] = [effectiveStart];\n  for (const slot of slots) {\n    candidates.push(slot.end + gap);\n  }\n\n  for (const candidate of candidates) {\n    if (candidate < effectiveStart) continue;\n    if (candidate + duration > windowEnd) continue;\n\n    let valid = true;\n    for (const slot of slots) {\n      // Our event: [candidate, candidate + duration)\n      // Existing slot: [slot.start, slot.end)\n      // Need: candidate + duration + gap <= slot.start OR slot.end + gap <= candidate\n      if (!(candidate + duration + gap <= slot.start || slot.end + gap <= candidate)) {\n        valid = false;\n        break;\n      }\n    }\n    if (valid) return candidate;\n  }\n\n  return null;\n}\n\nfunction computePrereqEndTimes(\n  eventId: string,\n  events: Map<string, Event>,\n  assignments: Map<string, Assignment>,\n  gap: number\n): number {\n  const event = events.get(eventId)!;\n  let minStart = 0;\n  if (event.prerequisites) {\n    for (const prereqId of event.prerequisites) {\n      const prereqAssignment = assignments.get(prereqId);\n      if (prereqAssignment) {\n        minStart = Math.max(minStart, prereqAssignment.endTime + gap);\n      } else if (events.has(prereqId)) {\n        // Prerequisite exists but wasn't scheduled - this event can't be scheduled\n        return Infinity;\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  return minStart;\n}\n\nexport function schedule(events: Event[], rooms: Room[], options: ScheduleOptions): ScheduleResult {\n  if (events.length === 0) {\n    return { assignments: [], unscheduled: [] };\n  }\n\n  const gap = options.gap ?? 15;\n  const sorted = topologicalSort(events);\n\n  const eventMap = new Map<string, Event>();\n  for (const event of events) {\n    eventMap.set(event.id, event);\n  }\n\n  // Try to maximize number of scheduled events using a greedy approach\n  // with retry: if greedy fails to maximize, try different orderings\n  const bestResult = greedySchedule(sorted, rooms, options, gap, eventMap);\n\n  return bestResult;\n}\n\nfunction greedySchedule(\n  sortedEvents: Event[],\n  rooms: Room[],\n  options: ScheduleOptions,\n  gap: number,\n  eventMap: Map<string, Event>\n): ScheduleResult {\n  // Try multiple orderings to maximize scheduled events:\n  // 1. Topological order (respecting prerequisites), then by shortest duration first\n  // 2. Topological order, then by most constrained first (fewest fitting rooms)\n\n  const orderings = generateOrderings(sortedEvents, rooms, eventMap);\n\n  let bestResult: ScheduleResult = { assignments: [], unscheduled: sortedEvents.map(e => e.id) };\n\n  for (const ordering of orderings) {\n    const result = trySchedule(ordering, rooms, options, gap, eventMap);\n    if (result.assignments.length > bestResult.assignments.length) {\n      bestResult = result;\n    }\n    if (bestResult.unscheduled.length === 0) break;\n  }\n\n  return bestResult;\n}\n\nfunction generateOrderings(sortedEvents: Event[], rooms: Room[], eventMap: Map<string, Event>): Event[][] {\n  const orderings: Event[][] = [];\n\n  // Compute topological depth for each event to maintain prerequisite order\n  const depthMap = new Map<string, number>();\n  function getDepth(id: string): number {\n    if (depthMap.has(id)) return depthMap.get(id)!;\n    const event = eventMap.get(id);\n    if (!event || !event.prerequisites || event.prerequisites.length === 0) {\n      depthMap.set(id, 0);\n      return 0;\n    }\n    let maxDepth = 0;\n    for (const prereqId of event.prerequisites) {\n      if (eventMap.has(prereqId)) {\n        maxDepth = Math.max(maxDepth, getDepth(prereqId) + 1);\n      }\n    }\n    depthMap.set(id, maxDepth);\n    return maxDepth;\n  }\n  for (const e of sortedEvents) getDepth(e.id);\n\n  // Ordering 1: shortest duration first (within topo order)\n  const byShort = [...sortedEvents].sort((a, b) => {\n    const da = depthMap.get(a.id)! - depthMap.get(b.id)!;\n    if (da !== 0) return da;\n    return a.duration - b.duration;\n  });\n  orderings.push(byShort);\n\n  // Ordering 2: most constrained first (fewest fitting rooms), within topo order\n  const fittingRooms = (e: Event) => rooms.filter(r => r.capacity >= (e.attendees ?? 1)).length;\n  const byConstrained = [...sortedEvents].sort((a, b) => {\n    const da = depthMap.get(a.id)! - depthMap.get(b.id)!;\n    if (da !== 0) return da;\n    return fittingRooms(a) - fittingRooms(b);\n  });\n  orderings.push(byConstrained);\n\n  // Ordering 3: longest duration first (within topo order)\n  const byLong = [...sortedEvents].sort((a, b) => {\n    const da = depthMap.get(a.id)! - depthMap.get(b.id)!;\n    if (da !== 0) return da;\n    return b.duration - a.duration;\n  });\n  orderings.push(byLong);\n\n  // Ordering 4: original topological order\n  orderings.push([...sortedEvents]);\n\n  return orderings;\n}\n\nfunction trySchedule(\n  orderedEvents: Event[],\n  rooms: Room[],\n  options: ScheduleOptions,\n  gap: number,\n  eventMap: Map<string, Event>\n): ScheduleResult {\n  const timelines = new Map<string, RoomTimeline>();\n  for (const room of rooms) {\n    timelines.set(room.id, { roomId: room.id, capacity: room.capacity, slots: [] });\n  }\n\n  const assignments = new Map<string, Assignment>();\n  const unscheduled: string[] = [];\n\n  for (const event of orderedEvents) {\n    const attendees = event.attendees ?? 1;\n    const minStart = computePrereqEndTimes(event.id, eventMap, assignments, gap);\n\n    if (minStart === Infinity) {\n      unscheduled.push(event.id);\n      continue;\n    }\n\n    // Try preferred room first, then others sorted by capacity (smallest fitting first)\n    const fittingRooms = rooms\n      .filter(r => r.capacity >= attendees)\n      .sort((a, b) => a.capacity - b.capacity);\n\n    if (fittingRooms.length === 0) {\n      unscheduled.push(event.id);\n      continue;\n    }\n\n    // Reorder to try preferred room first\n    const orderedRooms = [...fittingRooms];\n    if (event.preferredRoom) {\n      const prefIdx = orderedRooms.findIndex(r => r.id === event.preferredRoom);\n      if (prefIdx > 0) {\n        const [pref] = orderedRooms.splice(prefIdx, 1);\n        orderedRooms.unshift(pref);\n      }\n    }\n\n    let placed = false;\n    let bestStart: number | null = null;\n    let bestRoom: Room | null = null;\n\n    for (const room of orderedRooms) {\n      const timeline = timelines.get(room.id)!;\n      const start = getEarliestStart(timeline, event.duration, gap, options.startTime, options.endTime, minStart);\n      if (start !== null) {\n        if (bestStart === null || start < bestStart) {\n          bestStart = start;\n          bestRoom = room;\n          // If this is the preferred room and it works, use it immediately\n          if (event.preferredRoom === room.id) break;\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    if (bestStart !== null && bestRoom !== null) {\n      const assignment: Assignment = {\n        eventId: event.id,\n        roomId: bestRoom.id,\n        startTime: bestStart,\n        endTime: bestStart + event.duration,\n      };\n      assignments.set(event.id, assignment);\n      timelines.get(bestRoom.id)!.slots.push({ start: bestStart, end: bestStart + event.duration });\n      placed = true;\n    }\n\n    if (!placed) {\n      unscheduled.push(event.id);\n    }\n  }\n\n  return {\n    assignments: Array.from(assignments.values()),\n    unscheduled,\n  };\n}\n```\n\n`src/index.ts`:\n```typescript\nexport { schedule } from './scheduler.js';\nexport type { Event, Room, ScheduleOptions, Assignment, ScheduleResult } from './types.js';\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `npm test -- tests/scheduler.test.ts`\nExpected: All tests PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/scheduler.ts src/index.ts tests/scheduler.test.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: implement core constraint-based event scheduler\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Run Full Build, Lint, 